      • importInternalTables

        void importInternalTables(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar importFile,
                          CcddImportExportInterface.ImportType importType,
                          boolean ignoreErrors,
                          boolean replaceExistingAssociations)
                   throws CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException,
                          java.io.IOException,
                          java.lang.Exception
        Build the information from the internal table in the current file
        Parameters:
        importFile - Import file reference
        importType - ImportType.IMPORT_ALL to import the table type, data type, and macro definitions, and the data from all the table definitions; ImportType.FIRST_DATA_ONLY to load only the data for the first table defined
        ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
        replaceExistingAssociations - True to overwrite internal associations with those from the import file
        Throws:
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If a data is missing, extraneous, or in error in the import file
        java.io.IOException - If an import file I/O error occurs
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs

              throws CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException,
                     java.io.IOException,

        Build the information from the input and data type definition(s) in the current file
        Parameters:
        importFile - Import file reference
        importType - ImportType.IMPORT_ALL to import the table type, data type, and macro definitions, and the data from all the table definitions; ImportType.FIRST_DATA_ONLY to load only the data for the first table defined
        ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
        replaceExistingMacros - True to replace existing macros
        replaceExistingTables - True to replace existing tables or table fields
        importingEntireDatabase - True to replace existing database internal tables
        Throws:
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If a data is missing, extraneous, or in error in the import file

        Build the information from the input and data type definition(s) in the current file
        Parameters:
        importFile - Import file reference
        importType - ImportType.IMPORT_ALL to import the table type, data type, and macro definitions, and the data from all the table definitions; ImportType.FIRST_DATA_ONLY to load only the data for the first table defined
        ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
        replaceExistingDataTypes - True to replace existing data types that share a name with an imported data type
        importingEntireDatabase - True to replace existing database internal tables

      • importFromFile

        void importFromFile(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar importFile,
                    CcddImportExportInterface.ImportType importType,
                    CcddTableTypeHandler.TypeDefinition targetTypeDefn,
                    boolean ignoreErrors,
                    boolean replaceExistingMacros,
                    boolean replaceExistingGroups,
                    boolean replaceExistingTables)
             throws CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException,
                    java.io.IOException,
                    java.lang.Exception
        Build the information from the table definition(s) in the current file
        Parameters:
        importFile - Reference to the user-specified input file
        importType - ImportType.IMPORT_ALL to import the table type, data type, and macro definitions, and the data from all the table definitions; ImportType.FIRST_DATA_ONLY to load only the data for the first table defined
        targetTypeDefn - Table type definition of the table in which to import the data; ignored if importing all tables
        ignoreErrors - True to ignore all errors in the import file
        replaceExistingMacros - True to replace the values for existing macros
        replaceExistingGroups - True to replace existing group definitions
        replaceExistingTables - True to replace existing tables or table fields
        Throws:
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If data is missing, extraneous, or an error in the import file
        java.io.IOException - If an import file I/O error occurs
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs

      • exportTables

        void exportTables(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar exportFile,
                  java.util.List<CcddClassesDataTable.TableInfo> tableDefs,
                  boolean includeBuildInformation,
                  boolean replaceMacros,
                  boolean includeVariablePaths,
                  CcddVariableHandler variableHandler,
                  java.lang.String[] separators,
                  java.lang.String outputType,
                  java.lang.Object... extraInfo)
           throws javax.xml.bind.JAXBException,
                  CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException,
                  java.lang.Exception
        Export each table in the project to the specified file
        Parameters:
        exportFile - Reference to the user-specified output file
        tableDefs - List of table definitions to convert
        includeBuildInformation - True to include the CCDD version, project, host, and user information
        replaceMacros - True to replace any embedded macros with their corresponding values
        includeVariablePaths - True to include the variable path for each variable in a structure table, both in application format and using the user-defined separator characters
        variableHandler - Variable handler class reference; null if includeVariablePaths is false
        separators - String array containing the variable path separator character(s), show/hide data types flag ('true' or 'false'), and data type/variable name separator character(s); null if includeVariablePaths is false
        outputType - String representing rather the output is going to a single file or multiple files. Should be "Single" or "Multiple"
        extraInfo - Extra parameters dependent on the export format
        Throws:
        javax.xml.bind.JAXBException - If an error occurs marshaling the project
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If an error occurs executing an external (script) method
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs

      • exportTableInfoDefinitions

        void exportTableInfoDefinitions(CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar exportFile,
                                boolean includeTableTypes,
                                boolean includeInputTypes,
                                boolean includeDataTypes,
                                java.lang.String outputType,
                                boolean addEOFMarker,
                                boolean addSOFMarker)
                         throws CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException,
                                java.lang.Exception
        Export table type definitions to the specified folder
        Parameters:
        exportFile - Reference to the user-specified output file
        includeTableTypes - Boolean representing if the table types should be included
        includeInputTypes - Boolean representing if the input types should be included
        includeDataTypes - Boolean representing if the data types should be included
        outputType - String representing rather the output is going to a single file or multiple files. Should be "Single" or "Multiple"
        addEOFMarker - Is this the last data to be added to the file?
        addSOFMarker - Is this the first data to be added to the file?
        Throws:
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If a file I/O or parsing error occurs
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs

      • exportInternalCCDDData

        void exportInternalCCDDData(boolean[] includes,
                            CcddConstants.exportDataTypes[] dataTypes,
                            CcddClassesComponent.FileEnvVar exportFile,
                            java.lang.String outputType)
                     throws CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException,
                            java.lang.Exception
        Export script association data, group data, macro data, telemetry scheduler data or application scheduler data to the specified folder
        Parameters:
        includes - Array indicating internal file types to include
        dataTypes - The data type that is about to be exported
        exportFile - Reference to the user-specified output file
        outputType - String representing rather the output is going to a single file or multiple files. Should be "Single" or "Multiple"
        Throws:
        CcddClassesDataTable.CCDDException - If a file I/O or JSON JavaScript parsing error occurs
        java.lang.Exception - If an unanticipated error occurs
